Russian Night Wolves Motorcycle Club banned from entering Poland for a World War II memorial ride . 
  Polish authorities said last week they would ban entry to the Night Wolves . 
  The group vowed to enter anyway and 15 were seen at the border crossing between Brest and Terespol . 
  Many Poles view the pro-Putin bikers with suspicion . 
  The Night Wolves have rallied against the Ukrainian government and celebrated Russia's annexation of Crimea . 
  Vladimir Putin describes the bikers as his 'friends' The bikers want to travel across Eastern Europe to commemorate the war . 
 